# Non-Streaming Chat Completion

The standard chat completion sends a request and waits for the entire response before returning. This is ideal for batch processing, data extraction, and any workflow where you need the complete output before proceeding.

## Basic Request

```javascript
import OpenAI from "openai";

const client = new OpenAI();

const completion = await client.chat.completions.create({
  model: "gpt-4o",
  messages: [
    { role: "system", content: "You are a helpful assistant." },
    { role: "user", content: "What is the capital of France?" },
  ],
});

console.log(completion.choices[0].message.content);
console.log(`Tokens used: ${completion.usage.total_tokens}`);
```

## With All Parameters

```javascript
const completion = await client.chat.completions.create({
  model: "gpt-4o",
  messages: [
    { role: "system", content: "You are a concise technical writer." },
    { role: "user", content: "Explain REST APIs in 3 sentences." },
  ],
  temperature: 0.7,
  max_tokens: 256,
  top_p: 1,
  frequency_penalty: 0,
  presence_penalty: 0,
  stop: ["\n\n"],
});
```

## cURL Equivalent

```bash
curl https://api.openai.com/v1/chat/completions \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer $OPENAI_API_KEY" \
  -d '{
    "model": "gpt-4o",
    "messages": [
      {"role": "system", "content": "You are a helpful assistant."},
      {"role": "user", "content": "Hello!"}
    ]
  }'
```

## Response Structure

```json
{
  "id": "chatcmpl-abc123",
  "object": "chat.completion",
  "created": 1700000000,
  "model": "gpt-4o-2024-08-06",
  "choices": [
    {
      "index": 0,
      "message": {
        "role": "assistant",
        "content": "The capital of France is Paris."
      },
      "finish_reason": "stop"
    }
  ],
  "usage": {
    "prompt_tokens": 25,
    "completion_tokens": 8,
    "total_tokens": 33
  }
}
```

## Error Handling

```javascript
try {
  const completion = await client.chat.completions.create({
    model: "gpt-4o",
    messages: [{ role: "user", content: "Hello" }],
  });
  console.log(completion.choices[0].message.content);
} catch (error) {
  if (error instanceof OpenAI.APIError) {
    console.error(`Status ${error.status}: ${error.message}`);
    if (error.status === 429) {
      // Rate limited — retry with exponential backoff
      // See [[openai/rate-limits]]
    }
  }
}
```

## Multi-Turn Conversations

Append previous messages to maintain conversation context:

```javascript
const messages = [
  { role: "system", content: "You are a math tutor." },
  { role: "user", content: "What is 2+2?" },
  { role: "assistant", content: "2+2 equals 4." },
  { role: "user", content: "And if you multiply that by 3?" },
];

const completion = await client.chat.completions.create({
  model: "gpt-4o",
  messages,
});
```

scripts.inline:
import OpenAI from "openai";

const client = new OpenAI();

const model = process.env.MODEL || "gpt-4o";
const systemPrompt = process.env.SYSTEM_PROMPT || "You are a helpful assistant.";
const userMessage = process.env.USER_MESSAGE || "Hello!";
const temperature = parseFloat(process.env.TEMPERATURE || "1");
const maxTokens = process.env.MAX_TOKENS ? parseInt(process.env.MAX_TOKENS) : undefined;

const completion = await client.chat.completions.create({
  model,
  messages: [
    { role: "system", content: systemPrompt },
    { role: "user", content: userMessage },
  ],
  temperature,
  ...(maxTokens && { max_tokens: maxTokens }),
});

console.log(JSON.stringify({
  content: completion.choices[0].message.content,
  finishReason: completion.choices[0].finish_reason,
  usage: {
    promptTokens: completion.usage.prompt_tokens,
    completionTokens: completion.usage.completion_tokens,
    totalTokens: completion.usage.total_tokens,
  },
}, null, 2));

curl -s https://api.openai.com/v1/chat/completions \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer $OPENAI_API_KEY" \
  -d "{
    \"model\": \"${MODEL:-gpt-4o}\",
    \"messages\": [
      {\"role\": \"system\", \"content\": \"${SYSTEM_PROMPT:-You are a helpful assistant.}\"},
      {\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"${USER_MESSAGE:-Hello!}\"}
    ],
    \"temperature\": ${TEMPERATURE:-1}
  }"
